I am a proud third year cheer athlete with the Golden Flashes. I was honored to cheer for our football team in December at the Potato Bowl and our basketball team in Cleveland at the MAC tournament finals. As part of the Kent State University’s national cheer team I competed in April at NCA Cheer nationals in Daytona, Florida. Over 250 colleges and universities competed in the national competition. The experience was great. My interests include assisting others improve their stunting skills and spending time in Tierra Verde, Florida. Thank you for your interest.
